{"key":"post-10016925","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10016925</id>\n<content>Actually, plain rye DOES require a casing layer.&amp;nbsp; You don't need to wait a week after full colonization to use your spawn.&amp;nbsp; It's a good idea to wait a week after full colonization of fruiting substrates because it leads to a better and more even flush.&amp;nbsp; The mycelium needs time to consolidate its hold on the substrate.&amp;nbsp; That only means waiting from a few days to a week with cubensis, and a whole month after full colonization for shiitake.&amp;nbsp; If you expose to fruiting conditions early, it's a major cause of mutants and poor flushing performance.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10017453</next>\n<prev>10016839</prev>\n<first>10013700</first>\n<last>10017453</last>\n<when>1237694422</when>\n<utime>03/22/09 07:00 AM</utime>\n</post>"}